description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated and committed Registered Practice Nurse to complement the existing nursing team in this forward thinking 5 Doctor Practice based across two sites (Kings Norton and Alvechurch).  &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The candidate must be clinically competent in General Practice Treatment Room procedures. Be registered with the Nursing and Midwifery Council and hold a current registration pin number. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful candidate will deliver clinical care to patients using the EMIS clinical computer system. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The focus will be on the provision of:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cervical Cytology/Coil Removal &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Childhood and Travel Immunisation &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Chronic Disease Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wound management including Compression Dressings&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Infection Control&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Diabetic Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Asthma and COPD Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Person Specification&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;ARTP Spirometry certificate an advantage&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Holds a Cervical Screening Certificate &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Holds or working towards the Asthma and COPD Diploma&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Holds or working towards the Diabetes Diploma&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fully conversant with Quality and Outcomes Framework and Universal Patient Offer&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Holds a clean driving licence&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Can work in a changing environment and implement change as and when required&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The right person must be able to work as part of a team and also independently.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion about the post please contact&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(Diane Moseley on 0121 458 1342)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
